label: Hookworm, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of hookworm infection in a study participant, based on detection of at least one parasite egg in any of the stool samples. Up to three stool samples were collected per participant on consecutive days. Two slides were prepared from each stool sample using the Kato-Katz method and examined by light microscopy for parasite eggs.

label: Village study type
definition: Gaining control studies were conducted in areas of >25% S. mansoni prevalence in Kenya and Tanzania. Sustaining control studies were conducted in areas of 10-24% S. mansoni prevalence in Cote d'Ivoire and Kenya.
codebookDescription: Study Type: Gaining or Sustaining Control; Country wide
codebookValues: Sm1= Sustaining control study (Schistosoma mansoni prevalence during eligibility testing 10-24%)                                                                        Sm2= Gaining control study (Schistosoma mansoni prevalence during eligibility testing ?25%)
dataSet: SCORE S. mansoni Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Village study arm
definition: Abbreviation refers to community-level treatment in each of four study years. Gaining studies were conducted in areas of >25% S. mansoni prevalence and Sustaining studies in areas of 10-24% prevalence. s=school based treatment, c= community wide treatment, h=drug holiday.
codebookDescription: Study Arm: Abbreviations in arm descriptions: s= school based treatment, c= community wide treatment, h= drug holiday. Study arms describe treatment received by the village in each of the four study years. In Sm1 (Sustaining control) studies, Arm 1= ssss, Arm 2= sshh, Arm 3=shsh. In Sm2 (Gaining control) studies, Arm 1= cccc, Arm 2= ccss, Arm 3= cchh, Arm 4= ssss, Arm 5=sshh, Arm 6=shsh.
dataSet: SCORE S. mansoni Cluster Randomized Trial
